      <scopecontent id="aspace_e5dc518a21b02dbff5e03198a2042341">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>Collection contains personal and official correspondence, business papers, and family
            records. Much of the business correspondence deals with the sale and purchase of guano
            and the financial affairs of "Linden," the Filler estate. Filler was a livestock
            speculator, had interests in the marble business, silver mines, and livestock insurance.
            Included are letters from Woodrow Wilson, J.K. Vardaman, Gen. Marcus Wright, McAdoo, and
            other prominent national figures. There is also a manuscript account of the cavalry
            battle of Traveler's Station.</p>
      </scopecontent>
